{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|132","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":132,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":1,"text":"Lord, remember David and all the hardships he endured,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":2,"text":"and how he swore an oath to the Lord, making a vow to the Mighty One of Jacob:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":3,"text":"“I will not enter my house or get into my bed,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":4,"text":"I will not allow my eyes to sleep or my eyelids to slumber","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":5,"text":"until I find a place for the Lord, a dwelling for the Mighty One of Jacob.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":6,"text":"We heard of the ark in Ephrathah; we found it in the fields of Jaar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":7,"text":"Let’s go to his dwelling place; let’s worship at his footstool.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":8,"text":"Rise up, Lord, come to your resting place, you and your powerful ark.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":9,"text":"May your priests be clothed with righteousness, and may your faithful people shout for joy.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":10,"text":"For the sake of your servant David, do not reject your anointed one.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":11,"text":"The Lord swore an oath to David, a promise he will not abandon: “I will set one of your offspring on your throne.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":12,"text":"If your sons keep my covenant and my decrees that I will teach them, their sons will also sit on your throne forever.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":13,"text":"For the Lord has chosen Zion; he has desired it for his home:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":14,"text":"“This is my resting place forever; I will make my home here because I have desired it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:132:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":132,"verse":15,"text":"I will abundantly bless its food; I will satisfy its needy with bread.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01